{"expireTime":9007200804686247000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-de125ced3993963a986f8a46dd76154f-gatsby-remark-graphvizgatsby-remark-code-titlesgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-autolink-headersgatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants-","val":"<h1 id=\"gatsby-plugin-module-resolver\"><a href=\"#gatsby-plugin-module-resolver\" aria-label=\"gatsby plugin module resolver permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>gatsby-plugin-module-resolver</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/gatsby-plugin-module-resolver\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/npm/v/gatsby-plugin-module-resolver.svg?colorB=brightgreen\" alt=\"NPM\"></a> <a href=\"https://standardjs.com\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/code_style-standard-brightgreen.svg\" alt=\"JavaScript Style Guide\"></a></p>\n<p>Custom module resolver plugin for Gatsby</p>\n<p>This plugin allows you to add new “root” directory that contain your files almost the same as <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/babel-plugin-module-resolver\">babel-plugin-module-resolver</a> but for <a href=\"https://gatsbyjs.org\">Gatsby</a>.</p>\n<p>It also allows you to setup a custom alias for directories and specific files.</p>\n<h2 id=\"description\"><a href=\"#description\" aria-label=\"description permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Description</h2>\n<p>This plugin can simplify the require/import paths in your <strong>Gatsby</strong> project. For example, instead of using complex relative paths like <code class=\"language-text\">../../../../utils/my-utils</code>, you can write <code class=\"language-text\">utils/my-utils</code>. It will allow you to work faster since you won’t need to calculate how many levels of directory you have to go up before accessing the file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Use this:</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> MyUtilFn <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'utils/MyUtilFn'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Rather than that:</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> MyUtilFn <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'../../../../utils/MyUtilFn'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// And it also work with require calls</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Use this:</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> MyUtilFn <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'utils/MyUtilFn'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Rather than that:</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> MyUtilFn <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'../../../../utils/MyUtilFn'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"getting-started\"><a href=\"#getting-started\" aria-label=\"getting started permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Getting started</h2>\n<p>Install the plugin</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ npm install gatsby-plugin-module-resolver</code></pre></div>\n<p>or</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ yarn add gatsby-plugin-module-resolver</code></pre></div>\n<p>Specify the plugin in your <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code> with the custom root or alias. Here’s an example:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">module<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'gatsby-plugin-module-resolver'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        root<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./src'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// &lt;- will be used as a root dir</span>\n        aliases<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n          <span class=\"token string\">'@components'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./components'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// &lt;- will become ./src/components</span>\n          helpers<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./helpers'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// &lt;- will become ./src/helpers</span>\n          <span class=\"token keyword\">static</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            root<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./public'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// &lt;- will used as this alias' root dir</span>\n            alias<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./static'</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// &lt;- will become ./public/static</span>\n          <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This means you should be able to import modules like such:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/abdullahceylan/gatsby-plugin-module-resolver/master/assets/code-1.png\" alt=\"Code sample\"></p>\n<p>It’s great, isn’t it?</p>\n<h1 id=\"options\"><a href=\"#options\" aria-label=\"options permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Options</h1>\n<h2 id=\"root\"><a href=\"#root\" aria-label=\"root permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>root</h2>\n<p>A string of the root directory. Specify the path (eg. <code class=\"language-text\">./src</code>)</p>\n<h2 id=\"alias\"><a href=\"#alias\" aria-label=\"alias permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>alias</h2>\n<p>A map of alias. Aliases’ values could be a string or an object. If you want to use a different root directory for an alias rather than main <code class=\"language-text\">root</code> then you need to specify an object like:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  root<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./src'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  aliases<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">static</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      root<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./public'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// &lt;- will used as this alias' root dir</span>\n      alias<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./static'</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// &lt;- will become ./public/static</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In this example, Gatsby is going to use <code class=\"language-text\">/public</code> directory as <code class=\"language-text\">static</code> alias’ root directory rather than <code class=\"language-text\">/src</code>.</p>\n<h1 id=\"license\"><a href=\"#license\" aria-label=\"license permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>License</h1>\n<p>MIT, see <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/abdullahceylan/gatsby-plugin-module-resolver/master/LICENSE\">LICENSE.md</a> for details.</p>"}